timeline.bodyText:
Please quote all variables in bash (https://google.github.io/styleguide/shell.xml#Variable_expansion):

  
    
      
        Suggested change
        
          
    

        
      
    
    
      
          
            
            $DIR/apply-site-xml-override.sh /etc/hive/conf/hive-site.xml "$DIR/hive-site-overrides.xml" || fail "Could not apply hive-site-overrides.xml"
          
          
            
            "${DIR}/apply-site-xml-override.sh" /etc/hive/conf/hive-site.xml "${DIR}/hive-site-overrides.xml" || fail "Could not apply hive-site-overrides.xml"
          
      
    
    
  

nit: you don't need to fail explicitly, because you run with set -e, so bash will exit with error upon any command that exits with non-0 exit code
timeline.author: findepi
